      bullCase: "The U.S.-Iran deal could lead to sustained geopolitical stability, unlocking new trade routes and fostering economic growth, particularly in Asia. Lower oil prices, a direct consequence of this deal, would act as a global stimulus, reducing costs for businesses and consumers, thereby offsetting some of the drag from Fed tightening. Selective industrial and export-oriented sectors could thrive in this environment.",
